es are a whole different subject...<br><br>Anyway, What Kommisar and I are looking at is a party.  Either perhaps by the lake in WC or maybe our usual spot over in the Oasis at the Spectre Island.  Of course, other spots are open to discussion as well.  But please, keep then close to a port spot.  Heh.<br><br>Now we're still in the early planning stages, but what we're looking at is a nice get together type party.  Everyone is invited of course.  But I'd like it to be in a fairly newbiesh zone so we can set up first aid stations to help out others.  As I said, everyone is invited, you dont need to have been on a raid to come.  You just need to want to have a good time and meet old friends and talk. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>As for times, that too is still under negotiation.   However, with recently events I do think we need a party, but perhaps not quite this soon.  So I'm thinking about mid October would be good, perhaps some happy Saturday or lazy Sunday about mid way through.  I do think a weekend would give us more time, but some people may be off raiding or gett xp, so the day and time are open for thought by you the people who'll presumably be showing up.  Heh.<br><br>Oh...the carrot.  Yes,  I forgot the carrot.  I dont pretend people are going to show up for this just because I'm there.  In fact, thats probably a reason to stay far away and alive.  Heh.  However, in addition to all this we'll be doing some lotto's for some spare trinket items we've collected AND some jewelry items.  We might even have some auctions.  I mean, who wouldnt want a dancing naked barbarian as their slave for the day?  For jewelry we're talking black sapphire necklaces, jacinth and maybe diamond/blue diamond resist gear if we can find some for fairly cheap. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Of course the point of this is mainly to have fun and hang out.  Well, keep tuned to this thread and we'll be getting back to you with more exact times and dates.  I just wanted to let people know that we are working on this and that your reagent fees dont just disappear into some black hole or my or Kommisar's pockets.  It remains, as always, a KCoG fund for all of you.<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>KCoG Plane Raid Liason <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwarriorrmog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorRmog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/27/01 1:09:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=255.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: KCoG BBQ and Stuff!</span><hr size=1> How about Nekid Ogre Dances?<br><br>/em Scratches<br><br>YOU have become better at ass scratching (34829)<br><br>GO OGRES!<br><br>RMOG<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/27/01 1:34:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=255.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: KCoG BBQ and Stuff!</span><hr size=1> I understand Verant has nerf'd ogre butt scratching in SoL.<br><br>Guess it was considered an exploit.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>